President Biden delivered a speech in the Rose Garden, highlighting his administration's commitment to environmental justice. He thanked EPA Administrator Regan and Secretary of Energy Granholm for their work and acknowledged the efforts of advocates and community leaders. The President discussed the importance of taking action on climate change and environmental issues, emphasizing the need to follow the science and include communities that have been disproportionately impacted by environmental degradation. He outlined several initiatives and investments, such as the Just for-Justice40 Initiative and the Inflation Reduction Act, which aim to address climate change, improve air and water quality, and create clean energy jobs. The President also signed an executive order to make environmental justice a priority for every federal agency and establish a new Office of Environmental Justice. He closed his speech by urging unity and emphasizing the importance of addressing environmental justice as a nation.